<MainLayout title="Track & Field Banquet Planning Guide" description="Complete guide to planning a high school track & field banquet. Awards categories for every event group, decoration ideas, and custom track centerpiece recommendations.">
  <div class="breadcrumbs">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/banquet-planning/">Banquet Guide</a> <span>/</span> <strong>Track & Field Banquet</strong>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Track & Field Banquet Planning Guide</h1>
      <p>Track and field celebrates individual achievement within a team framework. Your banquet should honor both.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-wrapper">
        <h2>Track-Specific Planning</h2>
        <p>Track teams are often the largest spring sport, with 40-100 athletes across all event groups. Award ceremonies need to be well-organized to keep momentum.</p>

        <h3>Track & Field Decor Themes</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>On Your Marks</strong> — Starting blocks, track lane markings, and race-themed centerpieces</li>
          <li><strong>Record Breakers</strong> — Display school records and season-best performances</li>
          <li><strong>All-Weather Event</strong> — Indoor/outdoor themed with team colors</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="product-note">
          <p><strong>🏃 Track & Field Centerpieces:</strong> Custom 3D printed track centerpieces available in flying track shoe, high jump, hurdles, long jump, discus, shot put, and javelin designs. Each piece is crafted in your team's colors. <a href="https://lakeshore-gift.myshopify.com/products/flying-track-shoe-track-shoe-with-wings-banquet-table-centerpiece" target="_blank">View Track Centerpieces →</a></p>
        </div>

        <h2>Track & Field Award Categories</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Team MVP</strong> — Most versatile, highest point contributor</li>
          <li><strong>Runner of the Year</strong> — Sprints, middle distance, or distance</li>
          <li><strong>Field Athlete of the Year</strong> — Jumps, throws, or combined events</li>
          <li><strong>Most Improved</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Iron Athlete</strong> — Valuable across multiple events</li>
          <li><strong>Academic All-Conference</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Recognizing All Event Groups</h2>
        <p>Track has many event groups. Make sure each group gets mentioned during the ceremony — sprints, distance, hurdles, jumps, throws, relays. Consider having a captain from each group briefly recognize their teammates.</p>

        <p><a href="/award-ceremony/" class="btn btn-outline">Award Ceremony Tips →</a> <a href="/banquet-planning/" class="btn btn-outline">Full Banquet Guide →</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

